mand and allowing for a price increase. The company operates a responsibility-based standard costing system, and the variance reports for February and March showed mixed results, with the production manager facing adverse variances and the sales manager seeing favorable variances.\"", "\"SALES CONTRIBUTION VOLUME\":\"Sales contribution volume refers to the total contribution margin generated by the sales of a product. It is calculated as the sales price minus variable costs, multiplied by the number of units sold.\"", "\"JIT INVENTORY SYSTEM\":\"Just-In-Time (JIT) inventory system is a methodology where materials are only ordered and received as they are needed in the production process. This minimizes inventory costs and reduces waste.\"", "\"STANDARD SALES PRICE OF A CAKE\":\"The standard sales price of a cake is $0.85.\"", "\"STANDARD CONTRIBUTION PER CAKE\":\"The standard contribution per cake after all variable costs is $0.35.\"", "\"MATERIAL PRICE VARIANCES\":\"Material price variance is calculated as (Actual Price - Standard Price) * Actual Quantity. It measures the difference between the actual cost of materials and the standard cost. Material price variances are calculated by comparing the actual price per kilogram of ingredients to the standard price per kilogram, multiplied by the actual quantity used. The formula is (AP - SP) * AQ.\"", "\"MATERIAL MIX VARIANCES\":\"Material mix variance is calculated as (Actual Mix - Standard Mix) * Standard Price. It measures the cost impact of using a different mix of materials than planned.\"", "\"MATERIAL YIELD VARIANCES\":\"Material yield variance is calculated as (Actual Yield - Standard Yield) * Standard Price. It measures the efficiency of material usage in the production process.\"", "\"SALES PRICE VARIANCES\":\"Sales price variance is calculated as (Actual Sales Price - Standard Sales Price) * Actual Quantity Sold. It measures the impact of selling at a different price than planned.\"", "\"SALES CONTRIBUTION VARIANCES\":\"Sales contribution variance is calculated as (Actual Contribution - Standard Contribution) * Actual Quantity Sold. It measures the impact of changes in sales volume and contribution margin.\"", "\"CRUMBLY CAKES\":\"Crumbly Cakes is a company that operates a JIT inventory system and produces organic cakes. The company faced variances in material prices, mix, yield, and sales prices, impacting the performance evaluation of the production and sales managers.\"", "\"SALES PERFORMANCE VARIANCE ANALYSIS FOR VALET CO AMID ECONOMIC CHALLENGES\":\"Valet Co, a car valeting company in Strappia, faced economic challenges due to a global financial crisis. Despite increased petrol and food prices and a decrease in disposable household income, Valet Co's actual figures for full and mini valets exceeded budgeted figures. The case involves analyzing the company's sales performance variance, considering factors like increased car repair business and the closure of a competitor.\"", "\"STANDARD CONTRIBUTION PER UNIT\":\"Standard contribution per unit for Full valet = $50 * 44.6% = $22.30 per valet; for Mini valet = $30 * 55% = $16.50 per valet.\"", "\"TOTAL SALES MIX CONTRIBUTION VARIANCE\":\"Total sales mix contribution variance = (actual sales quantity - actual sales quantity in budgeted proportions) * standard contribution per unit.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}